The space: Cool atmosphere. It was very busy when I got my coffee, so I didn't get a chance to scope it out very much.  The price: The cinnamon fig latte was good. I don't regret getting it, but I wouldn't pay $5+ for it again. The staff were very friendly and efficient.  In conclusion: It's a good place to get high quality drinks and relax if you're lucky enough to find an empty seat.  However, I'm mostly on the go and treat myself to higher end coffees now and again, so it's not my go-to but I can definitely see and understand its appeal to people living in the area.

Pavement is not only a great coffee place it also promotes sustainability much more than all other places I know here. I will always recommend this shop.

You could walk to Dunkin, Einstein Bros, or Mameleh's and pay less money for an equivalent bagel - the cream cheese is what made this place the best! Lastly, bagels/sandwiches should be included in the rewards program. They are more expensive than a cup of coffee.

Where did it all go wrong?  Before Pavement, there was Expresso Royal; it was the beacon of hipsterness near BU, but they served the best egg, sausage, and cheese sandwich this side of the Mississippi. I went back this week to find a newly renovated cafe now called Pavement. Its not just the interior that has changed.  The service is terrible. I ordered two egg sandwiches to find that 'Sausage' is now banned from the coffee shop...even though its on the menu. Its took us 45 minutes to get our sandwiches. When we got them they had bacon in them even though we ordered ham...when we talked to the staff we got a nasty look and even got attitude. It took another 10 minutes to get sandwiches..When we got them back they took the bacon off and replaced it with ham...I could still see chunks of bacon on the sandwiches. Isn't this a health code violation, aren't they supposed to make new sandwiches?  Terrible experience, terrible food, and terrible service.
